HEADWORD: Micaceo-calcareous
<hw>Mi*ca`ce*o-cal*ca"re*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Partaking of the nature of, or consisting of,
mica and lime; -- applied to a mica schist containing carbonate of
lime.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Micaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
